The first stage of product design is the ideation stage. This is where the designer comes up with ideas for the product. The designer may come up with ideas based on their own experiences, or they may come up with ideas based on research they have done.
The second stage of product design is the concept stage. This is where the designer takes the ideas from the ideation stage and turns them into concepts. The designer may create sketches or models of the product at this stage.
The third stage of product design is the prototyping stage. This is where the designer creates a prototype of the product. The prototype is a physical representation of the product, and it is used to test the product and make sure it works as intended.
